mim.author: emagnso
mim.name: ReqAntennaSystem
mim.description: This MO represents a hardware unit installed in the antenna system that can be controlled and supervised by the system.

structMember.name: ifBandwidth
structMember.description: Intermediate filter bandwidth. It must match the bandwidth of the operator band.

structMember.name: ulAirFrequency
structMember.description: Absolute air frequency for the uplink carrier received at the unit.

structMember.name: ulFeederFrequency
structMember.description: Absolute frequency for the uplink feeder carrier (after frequency shifting).

enumMember.name: LTE_5MHZ
enumMember.description: LTE 5MHz carrier.

enumMember.name: LTE_10MHZ
enumMember.description: LTE 10 MHz carrier.

enumMember.name: WCDMA_1_CHANNEL
enumMember.description: WCDMA with 1 channel.

enumMember.name: WCDMA_2_CHANNELS
enumMember.description: WCDMA with 2 channels.

enumMember.name: LTE_MIXED_WITH_WCDMA_IN_10MHZ
enumMember.description: Mixed Mode, LTE and WCDMA within 10 MHz. LTE in channelNumber1, WCDMA in channelNumber2.

enumMember.name: TMA
enumMember.description: Tower mounted amplifier.

enumMember.name: TMF
enumMember.description: Tower mounted amplifier with frequency shift.

enumMember.name: PSI_CONFIGURATION
enumMember.description: Supported with Psi coverage.

enumMember.name: Y_CONFIGURATION
enumMember.description: Supported with Y coverage.

enum.name: AvailStatus
enum.description: The availability status is used to qualify the operational state. It indicates why the operational state has changed its value.

enumMember.name: IN_TEST
enumMember.description: The resource is undergoing a test procedure. If the administrative state is locked or shutting down, normal users are prevented from using the resource.

enumMember.name: FAILED
enumMember.description: The resource has an internal fault that prevents it from operating.

enumMember.name: POWER_OFF
enumMember.description: The resource requires power to be applied and is not powered on.

enumMember.name: OFF_LINE
enumMember.description: The resource requires a routine operation to be performed. This routine operation is to place the resource online and make it available for use. The operation may be manual or automatic, or both. The operational state is disabled.

enumMember.name: OFF_DUTY
enumMember.description: The resource has been made inactive by an internal control process.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY
enumMember.description: The resource cannot operate because some other resource on which it depends is unavailable.

enumMember.name: DEGRADED
enumMember.description: The service available from the resource is degraded in some respect.

enumMember.name: NOT_INSTALLED
enumMember.description: The resource represented by the managed object is not present, or is incomplete.

enumMember.name: LOG_FULL
enumMember.description: Indicates a log full condition. The semantics are defined in CCITT Rec. X.735 | ISO/IEC 10164-6.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_LOCKED
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is locked. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency locked.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_FAILED
enumMember.description: The availability status of a resource that this resource depends on is failed or dependency failed.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_SHUTTINGDOWN
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is shutting down. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency shutting down.

enumMember.name: LOCKED
enumMember.description: The resource is administratively prohibited from performing services for its users.

enumMember.name: UNLOCKED
enumMember.description: The resource is administratively permitted to perform services for its users. This is independent of its inherent operability.

enumMember.name: SHUTTINGDOWN
enumMember.description: Use of the resource is administratively permitted to existing instances of use only. While the system remains in the shutting down state the manager may at any time cause the managed object to revert to the locked state.

enumMember.name: DISABLED
enumMember.description: The resource is totally inoperable.

enumMember.name: ENABLED
enumMember.description: The resource is partially or fully operable.

enum.name: VerticalBeamWidthMode
enum.description: Vertical beam width mode of radio.

enumMember.name: NARROW
enumMember.description: Narrow vertical beam width of radio.

enumMember.name: WIDE
enumMember.description: Wide vertical beam width of radio.

enum.name: BeamformingPortMapping
enum.description: This enum is used to select between co-polarized and cross-polarized beamforming antenna port mapping.

class.name: AntennaUnitGroup
class.description: This MO is a container of references to the antenna and antenna near products (RET/TMA) serving a Sector.

attribute.name: antennaUnitGroupId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: positionInformation
attribute.description: Information on where the antenna unit group is located. This can be expressed in terms of a street address, building, floor, room, etc.

attribute.name: positionRef
attribute.description: Reference to a HW group that the antenna unit group is located in.

class.name: RfBranch
class.description: This MO represents the connection from an antenna feeder port on the RU to one antenna feeder connector on one or several antenna units. The MO represents all equipment between the radio and the antenna which isn't modelled by any other MO. That includes feeder, filters and non-supervised, non-controlled TMA.

attribute.name: rfBranchId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN. To provision the RfBranch not to be used for Tx transmission, even though it might be Tx-capable, the RfBranchId value should follow the format: "any_string"_NO_TX

attribute.name: auPortRef
attribute.description: Refers to the AuPort MO that represents the physical antenna feeder connector on the antenna unit, to which this RfBranch is connected.

attribute.name: dlAttenuation
attribute.description:
Downlink attenuation between the connector on the radio and the connector on the antenna unit. The attenuation includes feeder, filters, and non-supervised, uncontrolled Tower Mounted Amplifiers (TMAs). The sequence contains 40 entries and each entry represents one 5-MHz interval. The first entry represents the attenuation value of the lowest frequency interval in the operating band, and so on. The number of intervals depends on the operating band. For information on different operating bands, refer to 3GPP TS 36.104. The value range for each entry is -500 to -2, -1, 0-500 (-50 to 50 dB). Unused entries are set to -1.
Attribute is optionally replaced by dlAttenuationPerFqRange for configurations with radio supporting single band per RfPort. Attribute is replaced by dlAttenuationPerFqRange for configurations with radio supporting dual band per RfPort.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.
attribute.takesEffect: If cell is locked, takes effect when cell is unlocked. If cell is unlocked, takes effect immediately.

attribute.name: dlTrafficDelay
attribute.description:
Downlink traffic delay between the connector on the radio and the connector on the antenna unit. The delay includes feeder, filter, and non-supervised, uncontrolled Tower Mounted Amplifiers (TMAs). The sequence contains 40 entries and each entry represents one 5-MHz interval. The first entry represents the traffic delay value of the lowest frequency interval in the operating band, and so on. The number of intervals used depends on the operating band. For information on the different operating bands, refer to 3GPP TS 36.104. The value range for each entry is 0-800000 (0-800000 ns). Unused entries are set to -1. NOTE: The range supported by the actual Radio Unit may be smaller and must be considered when configuring the antenna system.
Attribute is optionally replaced by dlTrafficDelayPerFqRange for configurations with radio supporting single band per RfPort. Attribute is replaced by dlTrafficDelayPerFqRange for configurations with radio supporting dual band per RfPort.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.
attribute.takesEffect: If cell is locked, takes effect when cell is unlocked. If cell is unlocked, takes effect immediately.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: rfPortRef
attribute.description: Refers to the RfPort MO that represents the physical antenna feeder connector on the Radio Unit (RU)/Remote Radio Unit (RRU), to which this RfBranch is connected.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of the SectorEquipmentFunction

attribute.name: tmaRef
attribute.description: Reference to a possible TMA that is connected to this RfBranch.

The attenuation includes feeder, filters, and non-supervised, uncontrolled Tower Mounted Amplifiers (TMAs). The sequence contains 40 entries and each entry represents one 5-MHz interval. attribute.name: dlAttenuationPerFqRange
attribute.description:
Attribute optionally replaces dlAttenuation for configurations with radio supporting single band per RfPort. Attribute replaces dlAttenuation for configurations with radio supporting dual band per RfPort.
Attribute is used to configure DL attenuation between radio connector and antenna unit connector. Attenuation includes feeder, filters, and non-supervised, uncontrolled TMAs. Attenuation value is valid for full frequency range.
Attribute is a sequence containing 2 entries. One is configured while other is set to -1 (unused). - Use first entry to configure attenuation for first frequency range in dlFrequencyRanges of RfPort to which RfBranch refers. - Use second entry to configure attenuation for second frequency range in dlFrequencyRanges of RfPort to which RfBranch refers (only applicable for dual band radios).
The value range for each entry is -500 to -2, -1, 0-500 (-50 to 50 dB). Unused entries are set to -1. For information on different operating bands, refer to 3GPP TS 36.104.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.
attribute.takesEffect: Immediately if cell is unlocked, otherwise when cell is unlocked.

class.name: AntennaNearUnit
class.description: This MO represents a hardware unit installed in the antenna system that can be controlled and supervised by the system.

action.name: downloadSoftware
action.description: Fetches the Antenna Near Unit SW package from an FTP server and downloads the firmware file to the Antenna Near Unit. The Antenna Near Unit will run on the new firmware when the action is completed.

parameter.name: server
parameter.description: The IP address or hostname of the FTP server.

parameter.name: path
parameter.description: The file path to the software on the FTP server.

parameter.name: userName
parameter.description: User name used to logon to the FTP server.

parameter.name: password
parameter.description: Password used to logon to the FTP server.

action.name: readUserData
action.description: The Antenna Near Unit answers with user-specific data stored in the non-volatile memory reserved for such purpose.

parameter.name: memoryOffset
parameter.description: The memory offset to calculate the relative memory address to point the user data area where the required information is stored.

parameter.name: numberOfOctetsToRead
parameter.description: The number of octets to be read from that relative memory address. It must be less or equal than 70.

action.name: selfTest
action.description: The Antenna Near Unit will execute an implementation-specific test procedure of its own performance (that is, of physical and processor functions).

action.name: writeUserData
action.description: The AntennaNearUnit shall store user data in non-volatile memory. The data is stored in the user data area using the relative memory address offset given in the initiating message and starting with zero.

parameter.name: memoryOffset
parameter.description: The memory offset to calculate the relative memory address to point the user data area where the required information will be stored.

parameter.name: numberOfOctetsToWrite
parameter.description: The number of octets to be written starting on that relative memory address. It must be less or equal than 68.

parameter.name: userDataW
parameter.description: numerOfOctetsToWrite octets containing User Specific data to be written in the non-volatile memory area of the ANU.

action.name: sendTmfConfigurationFile
action.description: Configures a TMF (TmaSubUnit with tmaType = TMF) based on a TMF configuration file which is fetched from an FTP server and pushed down to the TMF. The TMF will run with the new settings when the action is completed.

parameter.name: server
parameter.description: IP address or hostname of the FTP server.

parameter.name: path
parameter.description: File path to the TMF configuration file on the FTP server.

parameter.name: userName
parameter.description: User name used to logon to the FTP server.

parameter.name: password
parameter.description: Password used to logon to the FTP server.

action.disturbances: Running the action will cause the sector and hence the cell to become disabled. All traffic in the cell will be lost.
action.precondition: tmaType of corresponding TmaSubUnit MOs must be TMF.

attribute.name: antennaNearUnitId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: anuType
attribute.description: Indicates if the antenna near unit is an IUANT or an Ericsson proprietary antenna unit.
attribute.statusInformation: Deprecated since L17A. Further support only to IUANT option
attribute.dependencies: If IUANT is set then the attribute iuantDeviceType needs to be set to a value specified in section 4.7 in 3GPP 25.462 as well.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: hardwareVersion
attribute.description: The hardware version of the Antenna Near Unit.

attribute.name: iuantDeviceType
attribute.description:
Type of IUANT-compliant antenna line device.
Takes its value from section 4.7 of 3GPP TS 25.462 (after conversion from hex to decimal):
- 1 indicates single-antenna Remote Electrical Tilt (RET) device - 2 indicates tower mounted amplifier - 17 indicates multi-antenna RET device
NOTE: 3GPP TS 25.462 defines device types by providing hexadecimal codes. The code must be converted to decimal in order to be used. If multi-Antenna RET Device is indicated as 0x11HEX in 3GPP TS 25.462, the decimal equivalent 17 must be used here.

attribute.name: onUnitUniqueId
attribute.description: The unique ID reported by the physical antenna near unit. The first two characters of the ID are the vendor code. The value is extracted from the response message sent by the antenna near unit during connection establishment. 3GPP TS 25.462 specifies the procedure in detail.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational State.

attribute.name: productNumber
attribute.description: Uniquely identifies the model of Antenna Near Unit.

attribute.name: rfPortRef
attribute.description: Refers to an instance of an RfPort from which this antenna near unit is controlled and supplied with power.

attribute.name: selfTestStatus
attribute.description:
The status of ongoing selfTest operation. In case no selfTest has been performed since last Baseband restart it shows state UNKNOWN.
NOTE: The selfTestStatus is not used to verify or confirm if a selfTest has been performed or not.

attribute.name: serialNumber
attribute.description: Unique number consisting of vendor code followed by a device serial number.

attribute.name: softwareVersion
attribute.description: The software version of the Antenna Near Unit.

attribute.name: uniqueId
attribute.description:
Subset of the unique identifier of the Antenna Near Unit. It is used to support advanced antenna system configurations, such as cascaded RETs. Leave empty when the units are not cascaded.
The value stated is a subset of the uniqueID(concatenation of the vendor code and the antenna near unit serial number) which must contain enough significant characters/digits to be unique among the antenna near units (with iuantDeviceType single antenna RET or multiple antenna RET) connected to the RfPort. See also 3GPP 25.462.
Some vendors use specific modifications of the serial number on the device label to define the unique ID. Contact the vendor of the antenna near unit (RET) to obtain the mapping between the serial number taken from the label and the unique ID.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state. If set to SHUTTINGDOWN, the state will immediately be brought to LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

class.name: RetSubUnit
class.description: This MO represents the device, either a single RET subunit or a subunit of the multi RET subunit providing for remote electrical tilting of the antenna unit where it is mounted.

action.name: forceCalibration
action.description: Force calibration of the antenna. Exercises the antenna drive unit over its entire range of travel to ensure fault-free operation and synchronize the measured and actual beam tilt of the antenna.
action.disturbances: This is a Time Consuming Procedure (TCP) that cannot be executed simultaneously with another TCP, while it can be executed simultaneously with a maximum of one EP. It may affect traffic.

action.name: sendAntennaConfigurationFile
action.description: Sends vendor and antenna specific configuration data in an antenna configuration file to the RET subunit. The antenna configuration file is fetched from an FTP server. The configuration data includes the relationship between the movement of the drive system and the beam tilt position of the addressed antenna.

parameter.name: server
parameter.description: The IP address or hostname of the FTP server.

parameter.name: path
parameter.description: The file path to the antenna configuration file on the FTP server.

parameter.name: userName
parameter.description: User name used to logon to the FTP server.

parameter.name: password
parameter.description: Password used to logon to the FTP server.

attribute.name: retSubUnitId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: calibrationStatus
attribute.description:
The status of ongoing calibration operation. In case no calibration has been performed since last Baseband restart it shows state UNKNOWN.
NOTE: The calibrationStatus is not used to verify or confirm if the RET subunit is calibrated or not. The RET subunit is calibrated unless an alarm indicates otherwise.

attribute.name: electricalAntennaTilt
attribute.description:
Electrically-controlled tilt of main beam maximum with respect to direction orthogonal to antenna element axis (see 3GPP TS 25.466). Value is signed; tilt down is positive, tilt up is negative. If electricalAntennaTilt is -999 at MO creation, actual value in RETU is used as antenna tilt setting. ElectricalAntennaTilt is overwritten.
Dependencies: RetSubunit.minTilt =< RetSubunit.electricalAntennaTilt =< RetSubunit.maxTilt AND AntennaSubunit.minTotalTilt =< (AntennaSubunit.installedMechanicalTilt + RetSubunit.electricalAntennaTilt) =< AntennaSubunit.maxTotalTilt Throws exception AttributeValueOutOfRangeException Disturbances: Change can affect traffic while the antenna beam is moving.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaBearing
attribute.description: Antenna bearing on the antenna subunit where the RET subunit is installed. Antenna bearing is expressed as bearing value x 10. This attribute is part of IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaModelNumber
attribute.description: Vendor-specific antenna model identifier. This parameter is part of IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaOperatingBand
attribute.description: Operating band used by the antenna subunit connected to this RET subunit. This attribute is part of the IUANT protocol specification and has no operational impact. Bit 0 in 0x03 is the least significant bit (For details on coding, see table B.2 of Annex B on 3GPP TS 25.466).

attribute.name: iuantAntennaSerialNumber
attribute.description: Unique hardware identifier of the antenna where the RET subunit operates. This parameter is part of IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantBaseStationId
attribute.description: Base station ID. This attribute is part of the IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantInstallationDate
attribute.description: Installation date. This parameter is part of the IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantInstallersId
attribute.description: ID of the responsible installer. This attribute is part of the IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantSectorId
attribute.description: RBS internal sector ID. This attribute is part of the IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: maxTilt
attribute.description:
Maximum electrical tilt supported by the RET subunit. The electrical tilt is defined as the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis. It is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt.
This attribute is part of the IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: minTilt
attribute.description:
Minimum electrical tilt supported by the RET subunit. The electrical tilt is defined as the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis. It is a signed value. Positive value indicates downtilt, and negative value indicates uptilt.
This attribute is part of the IUANT protocol specification (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: subunitNumber
attribute.description: Subunit identifier carried on L7 messages in which subunits are pointed with the help of application level identifiers.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaOperatingGain
attribute.description: Antenna gain for each of four operating bands, starting with the lowest value. This attribute is part of IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP TS 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: tiltChangeStatus
attribute.description: Status of tilt operation.

attribute.name: verticalBeamWidthMode
attribute.description: Vertical beam width mode of radio.
attribute.dependencies: Wide mode supported only for AIR4455 radio.

class.name: TmaSubUnit
class.description: This MO represents a TMA subunit which provides low noise amplification of the uplink received by the reserving branch.

attribute.name: tmaSubUnitId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: dlAttenuation
attribute.description: Subunit internal attenuation in downlink.

attribute.name: dlTrafficDelay
attribute.description: Subunit internal traffic delay in downlink.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaBearing
attribute.description: Antenna bearing expressed as bearing value x 10. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaInstalledMechanicalTilt
attribute.description:
Antenna tilt fixed on the installation.
Defined as the inclination of the antenna element axis with respect to the vertical plane. It is a signed value. A positive value indicates downtilt, and a negative value indicates uptilt. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaModelNumber
attribute.description: Vendor-specific antenna model identifier. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaOperatingBand
attribute.description: Operating band used by the Antenna Subunit connected to this TMA subunit. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact. Bit 0 in 0x03 is the least significant bit.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaOperatingGain
attribute.description: Antenna gain for each of four operating bands, starting with the lowest value. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantAntennaSerialNumber
attribute.description: Unique hardware identifier for the antenna where the antenna near unit is installed. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantBaseStationId
attribute.description: Base station ID. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantInstallationDate
attribute.description: Installation date. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantInstallersId
attribute.description: ID of the responsible installer. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantSectorId
attribute.description: RBS internal sector ID. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantTmaSubunitFreqRangeRx
attribute.description:
Uplink frequency band across the TMA subunit. It is a sequence of 2 values (16-bit unsigned) stating minimum and maximum frequencies for the TMA subunit transmission path.
Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantTmaSubunitFreqRangeTx
attribute.description:
Downlink frequency band across the TMA subunit. It is a sequence of 2 values (16-bit unsigned) stating minimum and maximum frequencies for the TMA subunit transmission path.
Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantTmaSubunitGainRes
attribute.description: Gain resolution on the TMA subunit subunit expressed in gain value [dB] times 4. Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

attribute.name: iuantTmaSubunitMaxGain
attribute.description: Maximum gain available on this TMA subunit.

attribute.name: iuantTmaSubunitMinGain
attribute.description: Minimum gain available on this TMA subunit.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: subunitNumber
attribute.description: Subunit identifier carried on L7 messages. While an antenna near unit is identified by one High-Level Data Link Control (HDLC) address (L2), subunits are identified by application level (L7) identifiers.

attribute.name: ulGain
attribute.description:
Internal uplink gain of the TMA subunit.
Part of the IUANT protocol definition (see 3GPP 25.466) and has no operational impact.

class.name: AntennaUnit
class.description: This MO represents an antenna unit that contains several antenna subunits installed with a common mechanical tilt.

attribute.name: antennaUnitId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: mechanicalAntennaTilt
attribute.description: The fixed antenna tilt of the installation, defined as the inclination of the antenna element axis with respect to the vertical plane. It is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt.

class.name: AntennaSubunit
class.description: This MO groups the antenna elements that, because of being controlled by the same RET radiate with the same tilt angle.

attribute.name: antennaSubunitId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: azimuthHalfPowerBeamwidth
attribute.description: Specifies the azimuth half power beamwidth for the antenna. In principle, for F band (1.9GHz) or D band (2.6GHz) antennas, the parameter should be configured to 65 degrees. For FAD antennas the parameter should be configured to 90 degrees for the F band (1.9 GHz) and 65 degrees for the D band (2.6 GHz). For information regarding antenna element half power beamwidth please refer to the manual from the antenna manufacturer.

attribute.name: commonChBeamfrmPortMap
attribute.description: Select between co-polarized and cross-polarized beamforming antenna port mapping. Valid both for the pre-defined antenna weights and custom antenna weights configured by customComChBeamfrmWtsAmplitude and customComChBeamfrmWtsPhase.

attribute.name: customComChBeamfrmWtsAmplitude
attribute.description: An array of eight or sixteen amplitudes for custom common channel beamforming weights. At least one of the eight or sixteen amplitudes have to be non-zero for the custom beamforming weights to take effect.

attribute.name: customComChBeamfrmWtsPhase
attribute.description: An array of eight or sixteen phases for custom common channel beamforming weights.

attribute.name: maxTotalTilt
attribute.description:
The maximum antenna elevation including the installed tilt and the tilt applied by the Remote Electrical Tilt (RET). described by the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the horizontal plane. It is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt. It sets a limitation on total tilt which is given by:
TotalTilt = AntennaUnit.MechanicaAntennalTilt + RetSubunit.electricalTilt
NOTE: If the antenna has no RET installed, this value does not account for the inclination that the antenna beam might have by default, with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis.

attribute.name: minTotalTilt
attribute.description:
The minimum antenna elevation including the installed tilt and the tilt applied by the Remote Electrical Tilt (RET) described by the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the horizontal plane. It is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt. The limitation on total tilt is found by the following equation:
TotalTilt = AntennaUnit.MechanicaAntennalTilt + RetSubunit.electricalTilt
NOTE: If the antenna has no RET installed, the total tilt value does not necessarily account for the inclination that the antenna beam might have by default, with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis.

attribute.name: retSubunitRef
attribute.description: Reference to the RET subunit controlling the tilt of this antenna subunit.

attribute.name: totalTilt
attribute.description:
Total antenna elevation including the installed tilt and the tilt applied by the Remote Electrical Tilt (RET). Total tilt is defined as the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the horizontal plane. Tilt is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt, found by the following equation:
totalTilt = AntennaUnit.MechanicaAntennalTilt+RetSubunit.electricalTilt
NOTE: If the antenna has no RET installed, this value does not account for the inclination that the antenna beam may have by default, with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis.
